
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates the use of the [add] slot to append nodes retrieved by [get-nodes] to a specific location in the node hierarchy. It targets the children of the [where] node within a [data.read] structure, adding nodes from the [.arguments] node. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to a specified location in the node hierarchy.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node to be added.
 */
add:x:./*/data.read/*/where/*
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
